trend_summary: Built-up cover rises moderately from earliest to latest images, led by industrial growth near the highway cloverleaf and scattered commercial/residential infill along the main east-west arterial. Road infrastructure and parking areas widen, yet a substantial southern greenbelt persists and even gains canopy. The landscape remains predominantly suburban, with medium overall density.
notable_changes: Expansion of warehouse and light-industrial roofs north-west of the highway interchange.
Widened ramps and enlarged parking lots surrounding the cloverleaf junction.
